// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/pragmas/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 6 (Connection-mode dispatch) / 5 (parser visibility)
// Spec: sqlite-native.md §18, Appendix F
//
// PRAGMA dispatch catalogue. Every supported PRAGMA carries:
//
//   * `kind`           — `PragmaKind` enum value
//   * `scope`          — connection / database / read-only
//   * `is_settable`    — write form (`PRAGMA name = value`) accepted
//   * `effect_phase`   — when a write becomes visible (immediate / on next txn / on next open)
//
// The L5 codegen translates `PRAGMA …` AST into a call to
// `pragma_dispatch::execute`, threading the per-connection
// `PragmaConfig` through the pipeline.
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.pragmas;

public module registry;
public module config;
public module dispatch;
